        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 900 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Genoa, or 7 miles south of Texarkana, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fulton, Pleasant Hill, Texarkana, Hervey, Mount Pleasant, Fouke,
Mandeville, Homan, Genoa, Garland, Patmos, and Wake Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
